                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.34/186: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-07-01T12:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1924—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Your no. 27, June 26, 4 p.m. Admiral Vogelgesang has requested me to inform
                    the Secretary of State that in accordance with the Secretary’s wishes the
                    recommendations for a naval program for Brazil made by the Naval Mission were
                    withdrawn for revision. In the revised recommendations all reference to a
                    concrete building program and any suggestions in regard to tonnage, types, or
                    number of units have been canceled and omitted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crosby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
